The paper discusses the extraction of 3D point cloud descriptors for computer vision tasks, which is a common topic in the computer vision (cs.CV) and graphics (cs.GR) communities. The use of 3D data acquisition devices also suggests a potential overlap with robotics (cs.RO). The evaluation of performance of state-of-the-art descriptors may involve machine learning techniques, indicating a possible connection to artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
